    <p>Tales Un­told (2020)</p>
    <p>Lo­cal indie pro­duc­tion Tales Un­told is a hor­ror-film an­thol­ogy fea­tur­ing four sto­ries – all shot on lo­ca­tion in Singapore. The black-and-white film ex­plores su­per­nat­u­ral themes while fea­tur­ing ar­eas known for their sin­is­ter past.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Sis­tic Live Stream WHEN: Till Sept 30 AD­MIS­SION: $6 for 48-hour rental pe­riod INFO: str.sg/J8DL</p>
    <p>How To Be A Good Wife (2020, M18)</p>
    <p>In post-World War II east­ern France, Paulette Van Der Beck, head of one of the most renowned French house­keep­ing schools, is known for teach­ing young girls how to be good wives and ful­fil their mar­i­tal obli­ga­tions. Af­ter her hus­band dies, she tries to cope with bank­ruptcy, young fem­i­nists and the re­turn of her first love as France grap­ples with</p>
    <p>May 1968, a pe­riod of civil un­rest. WHERE: Le The­atre, Al­liance Française de Sin­gapour, 1 Sarkies Road MRT: New­ton WHEN: Sept 26, 8.30pm AD­MIS­SION: $13 (Al­liance Fran­caise mem­bers) or</p>
    <p>$15 (non-mem­bers)</p>
    <p>INFO: str.sg/J8DE</p>


